\section{Failure Case Studies}
\label{app:failure_cases}

Table~\ref{tab:failure_cases} shows representative error cases for each
failure mode.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\caption{Representative failure cases from the 195-case audit of \memeic{}.
GT = ground truth, Pred = model prediction.}
\label{tab:failure_cases}
\small
\begin{tabularx}{\linewidth}{@{}llX@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Mode} & \textbf{Query (abbreviated)} & \textbf{Analysis} \\
\midrule
Polysemy & ``Who is the man in the suit?'' & Visual token ``suit'' retrieves
  business memory instead of the edited politician identity. \\
Conflict & ``What office does she now hold?'' & Image shows old role; text edit
  encodes new role. Model's visual prior wins. \\
Near-miss & ``What is the capital of the edited country?'' & Neighbouring
  country retrieved (geo-similar). Connector partially helps. \\
Multi-hop & ``What currency is used where he works?'' & Requires: edit(person)
  $\to$ country $\to$ currency. Reasoning chain breaks at step 2. \\
Hard-vis. & ``Identify the animal in this image after the edit.'' & Two
  visually similar species are confused post-edit. \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabularx}
\end{table}

